<LP>
   HOUSTON -- Western Co. of North America said it entered
into loan agreements for $55 million with Chase Manhattan
Bank and Den Norske Bank.
   The oil-field service company said it will use the
proceeds to retire its remaining Series A notes totaling
$46.4 million and for working capital. The financing is at
floating interest rates with a $25 million revolving-credit
facility and a $30 million three-year term facility.
